text.section:
Except as otherwise provided by statute, if an officer takes or receives a child into custody on an allegation of committing a public offense or into protective custody on being a suspected runaway, the child may be held at a police station, secure juvenile detention facility, youth alternative center, a nonsecure facility, or, as necessary, in a hospital or clinic for the following purposes:
Identification and booking;
Attempting to notify the parents or person exercising custodial control or supervision of the child, a relative, guardian, other responsible person, or the cabinet;
Photographing;
Fingerprinting;
Physical examinations, including examinations for evidence;
Evidence collection, including scientific tests;
Records checks;
Determining whether the child is subject to trial as an adult; and
Other inquiries of a preliminary nature.
